Namhla Mtwa, 35, was shot dead last month as she arrived at her home in Mthatha. It’s been alleged that she was in an abusive relationship with Major Mfesane Bhekizulu, who has denied the allegations. Mtwa’s cousin, Banoyolo Gqoli, talks about the relationship Mtwa  had with her alleged abuser, the night she was killed and misinformation in the media. Listen: The family dismissed claims made on eNCA by someone claiming to be Mtwa's  sister. “Unfortunately, this is not our sister and she is not from the Mtwa family,” her other cousin Siviwe Katywa said. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.